    parentName: "p"
  }, "secure"), ". "), mdx("p", null, "My parents make fun of me for this, but anyone who has tried to body surf in a bikini understands why bathing suit security is important.\nLast time I wore one in the ocean, I almost lost both my bra pads and my bottoms.\nI had to chart out a mental escape plan in case I got separated from my pants and had to flag my brother to come bring me a towel.\nIf I'm trying to enjoy my day at the beach, I don't want to have to keep checking if I'm still wearing pants."), mdx("p", null, "On the other hand, I like to look cute.\nBikinis are stylish.\nI like wearing them, and I like being able to show off my body in a socially acceptable context.\nIn other words, my teenage days of achieving bathing suit security by walking into the ocean fully clothed, dressed in a rash guard and knee-length trunks, are over."), mdx("p", null, "...And that brings me to all the symbolic baggage around bikinis.\nIn the bikini, you have a piece of clothing that is, all at the same time, 1) an expression of women's liberation, 2) a symbol of sexualization and objectification, and 3) completely mundane."), mdx("hr", {
